    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nI'm seeing errors like this using Cython 3.1.0:\n\n```\n17.85       Error compiling Cython file:\n17.85       ------------------------------------------------------------\n17.85       ...\n17.85       cimport cython\n17.85       cimport numpy as np\n17.85       from libc.stdlib cimport malloc, free\n17.85       from libcpp.vector cimport vector\n17.85       from libcpp cimport bool\n17.85       from numpy.math cimport INFINITY\n17.85       ^\n17.85       ------------------------------------------------------------\n17.85\n17.85       /home/kobold/.cache/uv/sdists-v9/index/691f29f8b22e69be/discretize/0.11.2/Gduk6MVRDTtkUk0kGfsGP/src/discretize/_extensions/tree_ext.pyx:9:0:\n17.85       'numpy/math.pxd' not found\n```\n\nI understand that `numpy.math` has been deprecated in 3.1.0 in favor of direct `libc.math` use, but it should still be available for now - and AFAICT everything else in the `Cython/includes` directory is present in the wheels. Looks like what happened is https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5842 removed the `__init__.pxd`, which causes it to be omitted from `pxd_include_dirs` when building the wheels:\n\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/6f03859fdeeac88a33f6b1e96cef58c09fd339ad/setup.py#L47-L51\n\nWould it be possible to put back an empty `__init__.pxd` here, or otherwise get this directory included again in wheels?\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\nfrom numpy.math cimport INFINITY\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n`numpy.math`, while deprecated, should still work.\n\n### OS\n\nLinux (docker build on a Mac)\n\n### Python version\n\n3.11\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.1.0\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
